Author: Marco KleinHeerenbrink [aut, cre],
    Anders Hedenström [fnd]
Description: Collection of functions useful for estimating/modelling flight costs
    in animal (vertebrate) flight. It features an implementation of the aerodynamic
    power model described in Klein Heerenbrink et al. 2015 Proc.R.Soc.A 471: 20140952.
    The package takes inspiration from the Flight program developed by Colin 
    Pennycuick (Pennycuick 2008 Modelling the flying bird. Amsterdam, The Netherlands:
    Elsevier). The afpt package allows the user to estimate animal flight performance
    based on basic morphological measurements such as body mass, wingspan and wing
    area; the package can be used to make predictions on how animals should adjust 
    their flight behaviour and wingbeat kinmatics to varying flight conditions.
Depends: R(>= 3.0.0)
Imports: graphics,
    stats
